{
  "$comment": "Per-attribute reporting granularity for the GEFEG BatteryPass-Ready passport, keyed by SAMM group then GEFEG attribute name. Each value is an ORDERED list of oec:DPPGranularity levels (extensions/common/core/ontology/dpp-core.ttl): the first entry is the primary/canonical level at which the attribute is reported, and any further entries are additional levels at which it may legitimately be reported. Several attributes are genuinely multi-level (e.g. carbon footprint is declared per model-per-site or per batch; manufacturing date is a batch fact also stamped per item; recycled-content shares are batch facts sometimes aggregated per model-per-site; material composition is model data that can vary per batch when sourcing changes; temperature information is a model design range at beginning of life and an item-observed value over life). Levels: ModelLevel, ModelPerSiteLevel, BatchLevel, ItemLevel. Model / ModelPerSite / Batch attributes are served by the GS1 resolver master-data resource (01 / 01+10 Digital Links); Item attributes are reconstructed by folding the EPCIS event stream for the serialized battery (01+21), see scripts/reconstruct-passport-from-epcis.ts. This is the machine-readable form of the level split in docs/EPCIS_AND_BATTERYPASS_READY.md. Coverage against the attributes the exporter emits is asserted by scripts/test-batterypass-conformance.ts.",
